Alcatel-Lucent, Cap Gemini, EDF, Eiffage: French Equity Preview

-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l   a n d   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 
2011-08-01T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-31/alcatel-lucent-cap-gemini-edf-eiffage-french-equity-preview.html
Shares in the following companies
may have unusual moves in Paris trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  France ’s CAC 40 Index fell 1.1 percent to 3,671.28. The
broader SBF 120 Index dropped 1 percent to 2,789.48.  Alcatel-Lucent SA (ALU FP): The telecommunications
equipment maker will be paid $70 million in damages by  Microsoft
Corp. (MSFT)  for patent infringement, a federal jury in  San Diego  said.
The shares fell 3.7 percent to 2.755 euros.  Cap Gemini SA (CAP)  : The computer-services company may
announce one or two acquisitions before the end of the year,
Investir reported, citing an interview with Chief Executive
Officer Paul Hermelin. The shares fell 2.4 percent to 34.375
euros.  Eiffage (FGR FP): The construction company said sales in
the second quarter rose 2 percent to 3.618 billion euros, as
higher revenue from construction and concessions made up for
declining spending on public works. The shares fell 2.1 percent
to 38.165 euros.  Electricite de France SA (EDF FP): The utility’s renewable
energy unit EDF Energies Nouvelles has entered exclusive talks
with Perceva Capital to sell its majority stake in wood furnace
maker  Supra (SUPR)  SA. EDF shares fell 2.0 percent to 26.465.
Supra shares were suspended at 17.44 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Gregory Viscusi in Paris at 
